                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5804</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Chinese Ministry of Foreign
                            Affairs</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Chinese Legation</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="67" xml:id="d45fn67">Copy of telegram transmitted to the Department by
                        the Chinese Legation on January 11.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-10">January 10,
                            1933</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Spokesman of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, in an interview to-day,
                    categorically denied the Tokyo report that in accordance with Chinese proposals
                    negotiations will open shortly for a settlement of the Shanhaikwan affair and
                    that General Ho Chu-Kuo will represent Marshal Chang Hsiao-Liang in this coming
                    negotiation.</p>
            </div>
